g.text: Electrochemistry: There it is, a brave little army in your pocket. The First Smokes Platoon. Twenty brave souls standing in salute, ready to step into the fire for you, sir...
You: No. Throw it away at the last second. [Ignore thought.]
Jump to: [Electrochemistry: "Already you regret it -- looking at..."]
Electrochemistry: ...bla bla bla. Boring. Light it up!
Electrochemistry: You picked the best one! This soldier is fat and succulent. What are you waiting for? Light up -- re-become yourself!
Logic: Will they *always* be looking, though? Because they might go to the toilet or you might be in a different...

Electrochemistry: Thick, warm smoke gets sucked down into your lungs. Immediately you feel a warm nostalgia fill your head, body *and* soul. A nostalgia for *yourself*, the man you were in your youth. Johnny Thundercop is back. And he's chill as balls.

Electrochemistry: Thick, warm smoke gets sucked down into your lungs. Immediately you feel a warm nostalgia fill your head, body *and* soul. A nostalgia for *yourself*, the man you were in your youth. Johnny Thundercop is back. And he's chill as balls.
Electrochemistry: Shut up. It's already happening...
You: What are the repercussions if I do this?
Electrochemistry: Repercussions? There's a high risk of GLORY? With a mild chance COOL *GENIUS*. Smoking makes you into an INTELLECTUAL, everybody knows that.
You: Dip that bad boy in the flame and breathe in.
Volition: It only lets you concentrate because you're in *nicotine withdrawal*. It only mitigates it's own...
Electrochemistry: Shut up and light that shit! You wanna be an idiot for the rest of your life? This shit will give you the cool edge you need.
Tutorial Agent: You've passed up your chance to start smoking CIGARETTES for now, but don't worry! The option to start smoking becomes available again in 3 hours.
You: I'm not going to do it. [Ignore thought.]
You: Pull one out of the pack.

Electrochemistry: Already you regret it -- looking at the pack... But don't worry. You can come back to this later. The army of smokes is honourable and faithful to you. You have your entire *life* to return to it.

Tutorial Agent: In the bottom right corner of the screen there's a CIGARETTES button! CIGARETTES give +1 to INTELLECT skills: Logic, Rhetoric, Conceptualization, Visual Calculus, Encyclopedia, and Drama. This is good before a White Check -- but damages your Health.

Electrochemistry: Get a load of this rock and roll cop here, people! Johnny Thundercop fishes a cheap lighter out of his pants. With a flick of the thumb there's fire, a primal satisfaction. Here we go...
Perception (Sight): The lighter's dark green, disposable plastic. Safety's off -- in your case, the safety is *always* off.
Horrific Necktie: Step into the light and be reborn in the cleansing flame, *bratan*!

Electrochemistry: Get a load of this rock and roll cop here, people! Johnny Thundercop fishes a cheap lighter out of his pants. With a flick of the thumb there's fire, a primal satisfaction. Here we go...
Frittte clerk: "Hey, you can't smoke in here." The girl's voice betrays little interest or enthusiasm. She doesn't even look up when as she continues: "Please don't fuck with Frittte."
Logic: It *will* help you concentrate a bit, that much is true.

Horrific Necktie: Oh yes, *bratan*! (The tie is shaking around your neck excitedly.) Please light up. You *need* a trooper between your lips right now! Calm your shit down. Go to Pleasureland. Become a *genius*!
You: I don't wanna light it right *now*, people are watching.
Electrochemistry: People are watching. What a pussy! People are *always* watching -- that's what makes it *cool*, now come on!
Idiot Doom Spiral: The man in the stinking tracksuit nods solemnly. "Having a well-deserved break from your adventures. It's what we all need sometimes."
You: I already had a heart attack. Maybe smokes are harmful?
Electrochemistry: No, what's *harmful* is fretting and worrying. It's the *stress* that's wearing your ticker down. The smokes will soothe it. They're medicinal.
You: Put it back in the pack. [Ignore thought.]
